blog.name: autonomy1
blog.title: Peter Percival-AUTONOMY
blog.description: Shades, nuances, scraps of existence......looking directly at an object can sometimes be a meaningless, even a destructive use of time…in society we are trained to look at things quickly, process that information and move on to another view…so much information and meaning can be lost in the action of moving on….by changing the expected angle of view, or re-arranging elements of an image one can derive another meaning from it, and if not an absolute meaning an abstract one which makes us look once again…that is all one can ask for, another look…(©) Pete Percival - 2013 All Rights Reserved. Reproduction of any kind is illegal.

summary: Day 07 - Free at last Another rendition of Jonathan’s end as it happened in my comic Last thoughts of a dead man. It’s my belief...
caption:
Day 07 - Free at last

Another rendition of Jonathan’s end as it happened in my comic Last thoughts of a dead man.

It’s my belief that while vampires may not age physically or die of mortal diseases, they are not immortal. Nothing really is. At some point vampires are not able to cope with the rapidly changing world anymore and either become insane and a liability to themselves and the entire vampire community, which will violently dispose of them. Or they choose to step into the sun to end their existence. Some vampires can become ancient though, like a few millennia old but that’s an exception. Jonathan got tired after almost 900 years.

✦ Like my work? Leave me a tip at Ko-Fi. Thanks so much ♥

blog.name: druubii
blog.title: Drew B.
blog.description: My name is Drew, and this is where I post my illustrations!  Here you'll find drawings, stories, fan-art, and general fun.  Feel free to drop requests in the ask box, or message me so we can get to know one another!  I really like tea, plants, and cats (typical, I know), along with piano music and pretty things.  I have a strong sense of adventure, and I love intense and gripping stories - especially ones rife with character development.  My hope is to create emotionally gripping content that you enjoy.  Thank you for dropping by my tiny corner of the internet!
